value.title: Biden looks to Susan Rice to elevate low-profile Domestic Policy Council
value.excerpt: "Susan will elevate and turbocharge a revitalized" council, Joe Biden said when he nominated the former national security adviser.

value.title: Trump attempt to overturn election is 'nutty and loopy', Romney says
value.excerpt: Utah Republican decries flirtation with Flynn martial law plan and suggestion conspiracy theorist Powell could be special counsel

value.title: Trump discussed naming Sidney Powell special counsel during White House meeting
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump held a meeting at the White House on Friday evening in which he discussed the idea of naming appellate attorney Sidney Powell as a special counsel to investigate voter fraud in the election,

value.title: Romney: Trump continuing to dispute election results is 'really sad' and 'embarrassing'
value.excerpt: Sen. Mitt Romney, R-Utah, called President Trump's refusal to concede the 2020 election "really sad" and "embarrassing" on Sunday.

value.title: Romney: Trump has a 'blind spot' when it comes to Russia
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Mitt Romney said Sunday that President Donald Trump has a "blind spot" when it comes to dealing with Russia after the President downplayed a massive cyberattack on US federal agencies linked to the country, warning that the aggression "is a big wake up call for us."

value.title: Surgeon General Jerome Adams cites antibody treatment for Trump's delay in getting vaccine
value.excerpt: Surgeon General Jerome Adams says the president has a "medical reason" for not getting the vaccine, since he was treated with antibodies in October.

value.title: Navarro: 'We are all China hawks' because of Trump
value.excerpt: As tensions between the U.S. and China rage on, White House trade adviser Peter Navarro told "Fox & Friends Weekend" that President Trump has pushed both parties to take a tougher line against China.

value.title: Biden will not discuss Hunter Biden probe with attorney general candidates: Psaki
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden's pick for White House press secretary, Jen Psaki, told "Fox News Sunday" that Biden will not discuss any investigation of his son Hunter with anyone he is considering to be the next U.S. attorney general.

value.title: Full Panel: Trump downplays widespread U.S. security breach
value.excerpt: Hallie Jackson, Yamiche Alcindor and Rich Lowry join the Meet the Press roundtable to discuss President Trump's response to a massive hack of government agencies and businesses reportedly tied to Russia.

value.title: Biden mulls punishments for Russia over suspected role in government hack
value.excerpt: President-elect will consider options for unprecedented hacking of US government agencies

value.title: Biden's impact on federal judiciary may be limited despite liberals' talk of 'court-packing'
value.excerpt: Beyond racial and ethnic demographics and job experiences, Biden's impact on the judiciary is not likely to be as dramatic as Trump's has been.

value.title: Trump downplays impact of massive hacking, questions Russia involvement
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump, in his first comments about a widespread data breach across the U.S. government, on Saturday downplayed the cyber espionage campaign and questioned whether Russia was to blame as alleged by his own top diplomat.

value.title: On ‘SNL,’ Jim Carrey Steps Aside for Alex Moffat, the New ‘Joe Biden’
value.excerpt: The comedy star’s high-energy impression of the president-elect polarized viewers. But other impersonators say getting Biden right is tougher than it looks.

value.title: 'Folks, we're in crisis': Joe Biden introduces environmental advisers

value.title: Jim Carrey hanging up his Joe Biden ‘SNL’ impression
value.excerpt: Jim Carrey is turning in his aviators and giving up his gig of impersonating Joe Biden on "Saturday Night Live."

value.title: Former US cybersecurity chief Chris Krebs warned not to 'conflate' voting system security with the SolarWinds hack despite Trump's claim
value.excerpt: Chris Krebs' warning came after President Donald Trump tweeted there could have been a hit on "our ridiculous voting machines during the election."

value.title: Trump claims China 'may' have been behind cyber attack after Pompeo says it was ‘pretty clearly’ Russia
value.excerpt: President Trump on Saturday claimed China "may" have been behind a massive cyberattack on U.S. government systems -- a day after Secretary of State Mike Pompeo said the attack was "pretty clearly" perpetrated by Russians.

value.title: The Trump survivors: Six Cabinet officials who stuck it out
value.excerpt: On Monday, Attorney General Bill Barr became the 12th of Donald Trump's Senate-confirmed Cabinet members either to resign or be fired by the President.

value.title: Biggest vets groups step up pressure on Trump to fire Wilkie

value.title: Trump promises 'wild' protest in Washington DC on Jan. 6, claims it's 'impossible' he lost
value.excerpt: President Trump on Saturday promised that there would be a “wild” protest in Washington D.C. on Jan. 6, as he continued to deny that he lost the election -- claiming it was “statistically impossible” for him to have been defeated.

value.title: Betsy DeVos stalled Obama's student loan relief program. Borrowers hope Biden will fix it
value.excerpt: Just before President Barack Obama left office, he made it easier for students defrauded by for-profit colleges to apply for the federal debt relief they had long been entitled to.

value.title: US Space Force members will be called ‘guardians,’ Vice President Mike Pence says
value.excerpt: The Trump administration celebrated the first birthday of the U.S. Space Force on Friday by announcing that its members will be known as “guardians.” Vice President Mike Pence made the announcement at a celebratory event tracing the development of the newest branch of the military over the past year.

value.title: President Trump, Melania Trump don matching tuxedos in final Christmas portrait: See the photo
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump and first lady Melania Trump donned matching looks and smiles for their final White House Christmas portrait.

value.title: Sir David Attenborough on Joe Biden, Christmas wrapping... and flamingos
value.excerpt: Like many of us, Sir David Attenborough has had to adapt to new ways of working since the coronavirus pandemic took hold this spring. For his latest series, the 93-year-old - who has been shielding - had to record some of his voiceovers from his home in south-west London.

value.title: Jeff Stein: Trump's last-minute push for larger stimulus checks example of 'long-running tension' with other Republicans
value.excerpt: In an interview on Hill.TV’s “Rising,” Stein said Trump had told allies that he wanted new stimulus checks as large as $2,000 per person, even as congressional leadership is preparing a package that would provide checks of just $600 each.
